Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.02,0:00:05.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Kingdom of Fiore...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.24,0:00:09.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A neutral country of 17 million people.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.66,0:00:12.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a world of magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.85,0:00:15.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic is bought and sold there every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.95,0:00:18.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is an integral part of people's lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.96,0:00:23.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And there are those who use magic as their occupation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.65,0:00:27.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Those people are referred to as wizards.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.98,0:00:34.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The wizards belong to various guilds \Nand perform jobs on commission.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.49,0:00:38.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There are a large number of guilds within the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.01,0:00:43.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And in a certain city there lies a certain guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.03,0:00:49.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A guild from which various legends were once born... Or \Nrather, will continue to be born long into the future...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.86,0:00:51.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And its name is:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.60,0:00:55.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fairy Tail!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.58,0:02:28.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Last time on Fairy Tail!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.30,0:02:31.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The reward is 2,000,000 jewel.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.33,0:02:33.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Intruder spotted!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.59,0:02:35.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're so annoying!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.53,0:02:37.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't give you the book!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.92,0:02:40.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe that Daybreak contained this sort of secret!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.70,0:02:42.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I've eaten, I'm all revved up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.21,0:02:53.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck kind of wizard is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.18,0:02:56.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Mommy, I can see fairies...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.32,0:02:57.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.62,0:03:00.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I should go find Lucy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.42,0:03:02.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who were these guys, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.06,0:03:03.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...we're mercenaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.70,0:03:06.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,An enemy of literature?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.81,0:03:10.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A sophisticated, cultured individual such as me, myself and I?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.83,0:03:14.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone who's happy to have a collection \Nof those freakish maids isn't cultured!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.77,0:03:18.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There is nothing to mock of my beautiful blond maids!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.63,0:03:20.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A treasure map?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.31,0:03:22.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A spot to hide valuables?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.20,0:03:24.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of secret does this book hold?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.56,0:03:25.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.13,0:03:27.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me or I'll snap your arms in two!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.86,0:03:35.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This girly doesn't get her situation!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.62,0:03:39.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I got Kemu Zaleon himself to write that book for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.15,0:03:42.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore any secret in that book is mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.15,0:03:46.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.35,0:03:49.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice one! Cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.08,0:03:50.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.99,0:03:52.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with this cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.32,0:03:53.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.48,0:03:55.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, get up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.73,0:03:57.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The water feels nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.83,0:03:59.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, it's sewage water.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.86,0:04:03.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dear Kaby!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.87,0:04:07.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The tables have turned!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.76,0:04:11.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you let me have this book, I'll consider forgiving you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.00,0:04:12.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I really want to smack you one, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.24,0:04:14.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A Celestial Wizard? {Note: I just call them Celestial Wizards -- it saves time and space, and nobody gets confused}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.91,0:04:18.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For a bookworm you sure misuse language!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.58,0:04:22.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"The tables have turned" implies that you have the upper hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.37,0:04:27.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But having one extra cat on your side isn't going \Nto be able to defeat my Diver magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.33,0:04:32.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So that was magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.46,0:04:34.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And that means Everlue is also a wizard?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.34,0:04:36.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And hey, you smell.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.84,0:04:42.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's written in this book!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.04,0:04:45.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A horrible adventure story with you \Nas the main character, Everlue!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.84,0:04:46.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.99,0:04:49.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's wonderful that I'm the main character.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.99,0:04:52.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But the story is crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.15,0:04:55.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For Kemu Zaleon, of all people, to write such rubbish!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.98,0:04:58.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a disgrace!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.70,0:05:05.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You forced him to write it! How conceited can you get?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.00,0:05:06.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Conceited?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.04,0:05:07.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I am a great man!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.32,0:05:12.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is an honor for someone to labor to write my book!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.53,0:05:14.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You blackmailed him to write it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.62,0:05:15.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Blackmail?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.75,0:05:17.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What about it? {Everlue considers it his right to blackmail the people he rules over}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.34,0:05:19.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It was his own fault for refusing me in the first place!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.50,0:05:21.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.59,0:05:27.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I told him to write a book where I was the \Nmain character, but that idiot refused!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.28,0:05:30.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So I told him:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.12,0:05:34.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Write the book, or I'll revoke the \Ncitizenship for your entire family!"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.93,0:05:40.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you did that, they wouldn't be able to \Njoin the merchant of craftsman guilds!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.00,0:05:41.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is the Count really that powerful?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.50,0:05:43.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, I'm a great man!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.98,0:05:46.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And in the end he wrote it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.33,0:05:54.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But I was annoyed by his first refusal, \Nso I made him write it in prison!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.01,0:05:56.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'm an author," he said! {edit: slight interpretation difference. Everlue is Mashima's example of how bad autocrats can become}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.39,0:06:00.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"A master craftsman!" But I broke that \Npride and haughty attitude of his! {edit: changed to match above}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.83,0:06:06.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you do such things just to satisfy your own desires!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.51,0:06:08.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You put him in solitary confinement for three years!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.56,0:06:10.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any idea what he must have felt?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.82,0:06:11.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For three years?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.86,0:06:16.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps he finally noticed how great I truly am?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.43,0:06:18.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.43,0:06:20.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He was fighting that pride of yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.03,0:06:23.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If he didn't write it, his family would be in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.59,0:06:28.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But he couldn't allow himself, as an author, to \Nwrite a book with you as the main character!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.97,0:06:32.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know these things, you pest?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.47,0:06:34.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all written in this book!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.04,0:06:36.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.15,0:06:38.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I read that book as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.07,0:06:40.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kemu Zaleon never appears in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.15,0:06:44.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that if you read it normally, \Nit's a work that'd make any fan cry!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.05,0:06:48.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But you should know that Kemu Zaleon was originally a wizard!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.65,0:06:51.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He couldn't have...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.16,0:06:55.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He used up all his remaining strength, \Nand cast a spell on this book.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.95,0:07:01.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So that was his scheme! When the spell ran \Nout, it'd turn into a book defaming me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.52,0:07:04.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,H-How rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.81,0:07:06.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You have no imagination, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.94,0:07:11.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that this book contains \Neverything about how it was written!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.35,0:07:15.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But the words that Kemu Zaleon left in this \Nbook were nothing so petty as that!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.71,0:07:18.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The real secret is something else!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.24,0:07:19.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.90,0:07:21.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The real secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.54,0:07:24.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'm not going to let you have this book.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.10,0:07:26.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, you never had a right to it in the first place!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.38,0:07:32.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Gate of the Giant Crab, I open thee!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.76,0:07:34.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Cancer!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.44,0:07:48.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Cancer!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.82,0:07:51.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a crab!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.78,0:07:58.28,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,[Note: "Kani" means crab in Japanese]
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.08,0:07:54.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure to end all your sentences with "-kani"!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.07,0:07:55.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You got to do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.15,0:07:56.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a crab after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.07,0:07:58.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just trust me! Say you promise!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.75,0:07:59.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to concentrate now. {edit: I think she was referring to herself, but this wording covers both bases.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.86,0:08:02.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't shut it, he'll pinch your paws.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.19,0:08:07.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy, how would you like your hair done today...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.41,0:08:08.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...-ebi?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.56,0:08:11.05,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,[Note: "Ebi" means shrimp in Japanese]
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.04,0:08:09.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ebi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.21,0:08:11.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you take a look at the situation, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.05,0:08:12.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're in a battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.20,0:08:14.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Beat up that bald old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.23,0:08:15.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay-ebi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.43,0:08:19.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it'd be like a straight jab, but \Ngo figure, it turned out to be a hook.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.89,0:08:21.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You can go home now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.83,0:08:22.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How about {\i1}you{\i0} go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.78,0:08:25.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The real secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.74,0:08:29.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be he wrote down the illegal underbelly \Nof my various business enterprises? {edit: I don't think that "hidden underbelly" conveys graft as directly as the subtitles need.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.68,0:08:31.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't have that...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.14,0:08:34.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If she hands it over to the Council's inspection wizards... {is this a consistency thing? is this group important later?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.43,0:08:36.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That'd be the end of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.37,0:08:41.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Gate of the Maiden, I open thee!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.33,0:08:44.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Virgo!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.47,0:08:48.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The same kind of magic as Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.78,0:08:52.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You rang, Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.29,0:08:54.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Virgo, get that book!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.30,0:08:56.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No way! She's a Celestial Spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.57,0:08:57.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ebi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.01,0:08:59.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.63,0:09:02.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.31,0:09:04.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is he with Virgo?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.35,0:09:05.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How'd you...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.80,0:09:09.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,After she started moving again, I went to get her and...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.82,0:09:11.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have a clue!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.75,0:09:14.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Get her... You mean you grabbed her, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.49,0:09:15.96,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Lobby
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.92,0:09:19.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He couldn't have come through the Spirit world with her, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.96,0:09:17.87,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Spirit World
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.87,0:09:19.45,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Sewers
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.45,0:09:20.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's unbelievable!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.29,0:09:23.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy, what should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.69,0:09:26.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do something about him!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.46,0:09:28.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Virgo, exterminate these pests!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.83,0:09:31.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.88,0:09:35.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll blow you away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.72,0:09:40.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Roar of the Fire Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.18,0:09:44.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You pervy mole!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.90,0:09:49.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't run away digging any more holes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.69,0:09:51.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A bit-part in a novel...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.73,0:09:54.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ebi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.82,0:09:58.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...is more than you deserve!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.32,0:10:03.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, what do you think of this look-ebi?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.77,0:10:06.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice one, Crab!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.58,0:10:07.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, "-ebi?"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.94,0:10:19.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice and flashy, Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.04,0:10:21.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You did us Fairy Tail wizards proud.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.44,0:10:22.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aye!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.07,0:10:24.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But we ended up destroying things again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.05,0:10:25.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this my fault?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.26,0:10:33.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.28,0:10:38.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The composition and style of this book is just awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.80,0:10:41.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There was no way I could image it having \Nbeen written by Kemu Zaleon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.71,0:10:42.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.47,0:10:44.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why I thought there was some secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.51,0:10:48.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What is the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.40,0:10:53.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I am quite sure I requested that you destroy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.16,0:10:56.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Destroying it is a simple task. You should \Nbe able to do it yourself, Mr. Kaby.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.71,0:10:59.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I will eliminate it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.13,0:11:00.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't even want to look at it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.33,0:11:05.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I know why you can't allow this book to exist. {Lucy didn't need to hear it. She figured it all out on her own -- As a fan, she knew Kemu zalion's real name, and had heard the name of Kaby Melon before}{uh, they had already left by the time he said that line.  Lucy didn't hear him.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.35,0:11:08.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's to protect your father's honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.91,0:11:12.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Kemu Zaleon's son, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.54,0:11:14.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.11,0:11:16.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you read this book?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.01,0:11:19.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I couldn't bring myself to read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.45,0:11:21.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's trash. My father said so.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.65,0:11:23.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why you wanted to burn it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.31,0:11:24.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.18,0:11:27.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Burn it just cause it's dumb?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.25,0:11:29.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that going too far, man?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.36,0:11:31.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Your dad wrote that book!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.26,0:11:35.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu wait! It's to protect his honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.54,0:11:37.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.55,0:11:40.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm ashamed that my father wrote Daybreak.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.27,0:11:44.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,31 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.42,0:11:48.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.21,0:11:52.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I'm late.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.36,0:11:54.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't contact us for three years!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.62,0:11:56.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Where in the world were you writing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.99,0:12:01.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm through. I quit being an author.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.20,0:12:03.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.47,0:12:05.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm never writing another book!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.68,0:12:12.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.47,0:12:22.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.67,0:12:25.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I tell you three years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.48,0:12:29.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you that you'd regret taking that \Ncommission for such a worthless book!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.74,0:12:31.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The money was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.13,0:12:33.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How could you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.92,0:12:37.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I finished that incredible piece of rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.99,0:12:39.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you smiling?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.87,0:12:44.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to that tripe you neglected your family for three years!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.82,0:12:50.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaby, I was always thinking of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.53,0:12:54.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why didn't you write something \Ndecent and come straight home?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.42,0:12:57.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You abandoned your pride as an author and your family!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.05,0:13:00.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You were correct to quit being an author.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.55,0:13:03.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone with no pride like you isn't fit to be one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.13,0:13:06.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Or a father.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.60,0:13:15.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My father died soon afterward.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.91,0:13:20.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And I've hated him... Hated him ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.48,0:13:27.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But as the months and years went by, \Nthe hatred I felt turned into remorse.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.64,0:13:33.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, my father is no longer in this world to apologize to.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.83,0:13:39.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So I felt the least I could do to atone \Nwas to destroy this last, worst book of his.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.32,0:13:45.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to rid the world of it for the \Nsake of my father's good name.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.54,0:13:48.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My father would agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.63,0:13:50.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he wouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.28,0:13:55.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's begun!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.80,0:13:57.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.89,0:14:01.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kemu Zaleon...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.29,0:14:04.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,His real name was Zekua Melon!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.29,0:14:06.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He cast a spell on this book.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.80,0:14:07.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.57,0:14:12.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dear Kaby?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.53,0:14:15.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! It's written to his beloved son, Kaby.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.50,0:14:18.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He cast a spell that rearranged the letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.67,0:14:20.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,On the entire thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.51,0:14:26.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.15,0:14:32.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason he quit being an author is probably not \Nbecause he wrote the most terrible book ever,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.27,0:14:35.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but because he wrote the most incredible one!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.12,0:14:40.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This incredible book is a letter to you, Mr. Kaby!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.43,0:14:45.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I was always thinking of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.11,0:14:53.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the true book that Kemu Zaleon left to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.83,0:14:56.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Father, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.30,0:14:59.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot let this book be burned.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.31,0:15:01.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess we don't need that reward, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.97,0:15:03.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aye!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.98,0:15:05.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The request was to destroy the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.92,0:15:07.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And we didn't complete it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.72,0:15:10.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.47,0:15:14.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... I mean, it's such a kind offer, \Nso why don't we take him up on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.56,0:15:15.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Greedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.71,0:15:18.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So much for all those cool things you said before.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.63,0:15:19.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's different!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.75,0:15:21.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't want it, so that's that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.86,0:15:24.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We do! I want it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.19,0:15:25.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.16,0:15:29.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You too, Melon. Go back to your real home.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.16,0:15:37.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe this!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.46,0:15:40.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it normal to just let 2,000,000 slide like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.11,0:15:44.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Taking money for a request that wasn't completed \Nwould damage Fairy Tail's good name. {the irony is intended}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.07,0:15:44.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aye!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.92,0:15:47.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But we did such a good job! Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.65,0:15:49.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And we're walking home?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.36,0:15:53.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Those people weren't even rich?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.66,0:15:57.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They said they just rented that house for appearances.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.87,0:16:01.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I would have taken the job even if \Nthey hadn't gone to all that trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.17,0:16:02.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.22,0:16:03.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I would have!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.55,0:16:04.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.48,0:16:11.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah, how did you notice the house wasn't theirs?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.15,0:16:13.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They smelled different than the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.85,0:16:15.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Anybody could have noticed that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.16,0:16:15.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aye.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.96,0:16:19.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm not an animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.00,0:16:22.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But I really look up to a writer like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.37,0:16:24.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.99,0:16:28.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That thing you were hiding...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.36,0:16:30.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a novel you're writing, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.22,0:16:32.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you know all about books.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.19,0:16:35.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Don't tell a soul, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.43,0:16:36.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.39,0:16:38.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm still really bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.12,0:16:40.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd just die of embarrassment if someone read it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.14,0:16:41.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, no one will.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.93,0:16:45.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't exactly make me feel better.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.93,0:16:50.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Wait a sec, are you sure this is the way?"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.70,0:16:52.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...she says.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.44,0:16:56.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Happy said to go this way, so this is the way we go," says I.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.52,0:16:57.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.13,0:17:00.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a cat, obviously!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.26,0:17:02.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Cat's have an excellent sense of smell!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.11,0:17:07.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Isn't that dogs? And what does smell \Nhave to do with direction?" she says.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.91,0:17:10.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, how about walking yourself, you lazy bum?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.30,0:17:13.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'm tired," she says.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.05,0:17:14.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.97,0:17:17.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.89,0:17:21.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Is he looking for a fight?" she says.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.81,0:17:24.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Go for it, Natsu!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.51,0:17:27.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Gray!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.58,0:17:30.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Why is he in his underwear?" she says.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.16,0:17:31.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I was looking for a bathroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.89,0:17:34.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you strip before you found one, jerk?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.44,0:17:37.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And there's no way there'd be a \Nbathroom in the forest anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.53,0:17:40.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And weren't {\i1}you{\i0} the one barging in when a \Nguy's going to the bathroom, you bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.45,0:17:41.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Exhibitionist!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.91,0:17:42.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are they, in third grade?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.86,0:17:43.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Talking matchstick!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.40,0:17:43.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She says!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.68,0:17:48.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see! You're coming back from a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.07,0:17:51.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Cutting through this forest is a shortcut back to Magnolia, see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.62,0:17:53.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,See? See, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.25,0:17:58.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You were bragging about your nose, but \Nyou didn't even realize Gray was there?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.18,0:18:00.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There are some things you don't want to smell.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.59,0:18:01.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.55,0:18:04.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough of you. Get on back already by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.77,0:18:06.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.03,0:18:08.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be trouble if I don't get back soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.07,0:18:09.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of trouble?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.66,0:18:11.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Erza'll be back shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.22,0:18:13.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Erza... You mean, {\i1}her{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.83,0:18:17.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The woman known as the most powerful wizard in Fairy Tail! {edit: the previous wording made it seem that Happy hadn't met her yet}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.46,0:18:19.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Awesome! I want to meet her!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.80,0:18:24.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But I've never seen a picture of her in a magazine, \Nso what kind of person is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.71,0:18:25.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.19,0:18:27.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wild animal?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.29,0:18:28.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Beast?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.31,0:18:30.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,More like an evil demon!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.17,0:18:34.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She's not {\i1}that{\i0} big.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.03,0:18:35.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But she's bigger than you'd think!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.94,0:18:39.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's about right if you're talking about how scary she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.39,0:18:40.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, maybe it's even worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.31,0:18:44.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Like, this bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.34,0:18:48.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I think she could blow away a mountain \Ninto 3 pieces with a single kick!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.77,0:18:51.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Three pieces is exaggerating, I think it's more like two.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.84,0:18:55.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A woman that can blow a mountain in two with a single kick?  {this line implies Lucy knew it was a woman}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.09,0:18:56.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's pretty scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.09,0:18:57.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, we've got to hurry home.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.46,0:18:59.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Crap, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.54,0:19:06.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A wizard?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.72,0:19:07.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.81,0:19:08.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aye...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.08,0:19:12.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna get us some protein for once!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.38,0:19:14.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sick of fruits and nuts!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.46,0:19:15.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Meat!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.58,0:19:17.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.05,0:19:20.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, this guy's shaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.30,0:19:21.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry 'bout this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.64,0:19:24.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess you're scared 'cause you'll end up in our bellies!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.71,0:19:25.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.73,0:19:28.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not shaking because I'm scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.22,0:19:30.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to go to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.16,0:19:33.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I might not be able to hold it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.05,0:19:35.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If that happens it'll make me taste weird, I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.46,0:19:37.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.  Do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.67,0:19:38.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Meat!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.37,0:19:42.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Medium, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.81,0:19:47.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stand it! Are you sure about this? I'll taste weird!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.01,0:19:48.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.53,0:19:50.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.62,0:19:51.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.75,0:19:53.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't taste weird!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.52,0:19:54.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're still going on about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.81,0:19:56.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got our friend there, bub. {these four lines all start at the same time}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.74,0:19:59.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You may be hungry, but we can't let you eat him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.74,0:20:01.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're also wizards, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.32,0:20:02.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,From what guild?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.72,0:20:04.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,None of your business!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.38,0:20:05.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Get 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.72,0:20:07.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Gray, let's do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.47,0:20:09.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't order me around.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.81,0:20:12.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Take this!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.54,0:20:14.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sand Bomb!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.73,0:20:18.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.73,0:20:19.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave him!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.70,0:20:20.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of Happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.72,0:20:21.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.36,0:20:28.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no! I'm going to be eaten by Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.04,0:20:29.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up, cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.24,0:20:32.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Meat!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.21,0:20:37.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Meat!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.88,0:20:39.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's next?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.62,0:20:42.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll get an unexpected visitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.13,0:20:44.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The stars point to trouble with water and women. {I love the foreshadowing of Juvia!!}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.68,0:20:45.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fortune telling?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.84,0:20:47.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.35,0:20:49.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not even using magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.24,0:20:50.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.18,0:20:51.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, your clothes...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.19,0:20:51.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.86,0:20:53.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.53,0:20:55.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.76,0:20:56.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Look here, you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.10,0:21:00.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you make my mouth all gritty!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.65,0:21:04.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Take this!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.31,0:21:06.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Iron Fist of the Fire Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.33,0:21:22.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to get serious against these small fry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.89,0:21:25.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How about I fry up that smart mouth of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.03,0:21:27.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt you could. Not with those lukewarm flames of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.54,0:21:28.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.43,0:21:29.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Baggy pants!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.91,0:21:29.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lulla...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.94,0:21:30.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ill-tempered!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.94,0:21:30.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.94,0:21:31.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sourpuss!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.66,0:21:33.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hothead!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.82,0:21:34.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The lulla... by...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.22,0:21:35.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.93,0:21:36.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lullaby?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.66,0:21:38.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.04,0:21:46.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.33,0:21:47.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.28,0:21:49.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't sense them anymore already.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.41,0:21:52.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's someone crazy fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.81,0:21:55.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! I don't get this at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.49,0:21:56.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lullaby?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.22,0:23:59.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I did my best but it was all for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.85,0:24:02.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But it seems like they really appreciated it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.53,0:24:05.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just do your best for the reward in your next mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.35,0:24:07.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right... That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.31,0:24:11.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So then, what kind of outfit are you going to work in next?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.67,0:24:13.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I think she's got the wrong impression!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.42,0:24:15.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: The Armored Wizard! {edit: Erza's magic is to "requip" armor and weapons, and because of a tragic past, she always keeps herself armored}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.93,0:24:18.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, I didn't wear it because it's my style, it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.59,0:24:22.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,After doing the maid thing, then it's a \Nbunny girl or swimsuit next usually...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.20,0:24:24.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to people when they're talking!
